Common CI/CD File Names
The specific name and syntax of the CI/CD file depend on the platform you are using:
GitLab CI/CD: Uses a file named .gitlab-ci.yml.
GitHub Actions: Uses YAML files typically located in the .github/workflows/ directory.
Jenkins: Often uses a Jenkinsfile.
Azure DevOps: Uses a azure-pipelines.yml file for YAML pipelines. 
about.gitlab.com
about.gitlab.com
 +3
Key Components of a CI/CD File
The configuration file generally structures the automation into a sequence of jobs and stages: 
about.gitlab.com
about.gitlab.com
 +3
Stages: These define the order of operations in the pipeline. Common stages include build, test, and deploy. 
about.gitlab.com
about.gitlab.com
Jobs: These are the specific tasks that run within a stage. A job might compile code, run unit tests, or deploy the application to a staging environment. 
about.gitlab.com
about.gitlab.com
 +2
Scripts: Commands executed by the jobs, such as npm install or ./build.sh


